# Testing Standards

## Context

- Provides guidelines for testing implementation and quality assurance
- Ensures consistent testing practices across the project
- Helps maintain code reliability and maintainability

## Critical Rules

- Write unit tests for all new functionality using Jest and React Testing Library
- Test user interactions and accessibility features
- Maintain high test coverage for critical components
- Use descriptive test names that explain the expected behavior
- Mock external dependencies and API calls appropriately
- Test error scenarios and edge cases
- Use testing best practices for React components
- Implement integration tests for critical user flows
- Use visual testing for UI components when appropriate
- Document testing strategies and patterns

